==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Starvation
<hw>Star*va"tion</hw> <pr>(st⟦aum⟧r*v⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of starving, or the state of being
starved.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ This word was first used, according to Horace Walpole,
by Henry Dundas, the first Lord Melville, in a speech on American
affairs in 1775, which obtained for him the nickname of
<xex>Starvation</xex> Dundas.⟦br⟧
⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Starvation</xex>, we are also told, belongs to the class of
'vile compounds' from being a mongrel; as if English were not full of
mongrels, and as if it would not be in distressing straits without
them.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Fitzed. Hall.</au></note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Starve</ent>⟦br⟧
